her tongue isn't coated,
and her throat isn't red,

33
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:44,850
she's awfully pale.

34
00:01:44,850 --> 00:01:46,110
But I don't know what's wrong?

35
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:47,310
Neither do we.

36
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:50,360
It's not like any illness
we've ever had.

37
00:01:50,350 --> 00:01:52,520
Could...could it be magic?

38
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:54,320
Magic, that's it!

39
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:57,940
When magic's involved,
the Moochick is the one to see.

40
00:01:57,940 --> 00:01:59,490
I'll take you to him, Megan.

41
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:00,840
Let's go.

42
00:02:00,830 --> 00:02:03,160
Just a minute, Megan,
I'm coming with you.

43
00:02:03,170 --> 00:02:05,430
- Me too.
- We'll all go with you, Megan.

44
00:02:05,420 --> 00:02:06,670
I'm coming too.

45
00:02:06,670 --> 00:02:07,920
Hop on Spike.

46
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:11,840
We'll be back soon Mimic.
Hold on!

47
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,760
Hurry back!

48
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:15,630
And good luck.

49
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:19,380
<i>(wolves howling)</i>

50
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:21,800
<i>(howling continues)
There, all safe and sound.</i>

51
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,020
Gee Thanks.

52
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:25,100
<i>(wolves howling and barking)
Wolves!</i>

53
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:27,050
Run for the Moochick's cottage.

54
00:02:28,270 --> 00:02:30,470
I've done it, Habbit.

55
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:32,650
Help! Open up!

56
00:02:32,650 --> 00:02:33,620
Whoever you are,

57
00:02:33,610 --> 00:02:35,230
go away, go away.
I'm busy.

58
00:02:37,150 --> 00:02:40,570
<i>(wolves howling and barking)</i>

59
00:02:40,570 --> 00:02:42,240
(gasps)
Nduh! No.

60
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:44,540
I'm sorry.
But this is an emergency.

61
00:02:44,540 --> 00:02:46,370
Wolves were after us.

62
00:02:46,380 --> 00:02:47,470
(giggles)
Oh! Ha, ha, hah.

63
00:02:47,460 --> 00:02:49,290
No, no, no, no, no!

64
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:51,800
That was my wolf box.
<i>(barking sound from the box)</i>

65
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:55,560
Oh! But it was supposed
to scare you away, oh!

66
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:57,080
Ummm...Mr. Moochick,

67
00:02:57,090 --> 00:03:00,310
Mimic is sick
and we think it's due to magic.

68
00:03:00,310 --> 00:03:01,560
Uh-ah, what?

69
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,850
She's lost her twinkle.

70
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:05,090
Can ya help her?

71
00:03:05,090 --> 00:03:06,430
Hmmm...

72
00:03:06,430 --> 00:03:09,400
Well, I'm sure I have something
about sick unicorns

73
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,980
in a book somewhere.

74
00:03:10,980 --> 00:03:12,270
(snaps)

75
00:03:12,270 --> 00:03:15,230
Aha! Yes this book
is the very one.

76
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:16,530
"Pony Legends and History."

77
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,400
(clear throat)

78
00:03:18,410 --> 00:03:21,780
"The Legend of
the Four Golden Horseshoes."

79
00:03:21,780 --> 00:03:23,670
Yes, of course!

80
00:03:23,660 --> 00:03:27,200
Ah! Mimic is descended
from this unicorn.

81
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:30,330
<i>"Long ago, in the land of
Argyte,</i>

82
00:03:30,340 --> 00:03:32,850
<i>four horseshoes were made
of mystical starlight."</i>

83
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:34,090
Yes, oh.

84
00:03:34,090 --> 00:03:37,840
<i>"They were placed on the
hooves of this special unicorn.</i>

85
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:40,960
<i>Now, each shoe gave her
a magical power."</i>

86
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,760
My, my, my!

87
00:03:42,770 --> 00:03:44,610
<i>"The first showed the future,</i>

88
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:47,720
<i>"the second had
the power of blazing light,</i>

89
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:49,600
<i>"the third made
another's thoughts</i>

90
00:03:49,610 --> 00:03:51,480
<i>"sound clear and loud,</i>

91
00:03:51,470 --> 00:03:55,860
<i>and the fourth let its wearer
float like a cloud."</i>

92
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:57,480
(neighs)

93
00:04:00,780 --> 00:04:04,070
<i>"Deep in dream valley,
the wind left her at dawn</i>

94
00:04:04,070 --> 00:04:09,070
<i>And there she did stay,
for her horseshoes were gone."</i>

95
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,330
That's all fascinating,
Mr. Moochick.

96
00:04:10,330 --> 00:04:13,220
But what does it have to do
with Mimic's illness?

97
00:04:13,210 --> 00:04:14,460
Well, my, my.

98
00:04:14,460 --> 00:04:17,880
Mimic is a direct descendent
of that unicorn.

99
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:20,800
And the magic of the shoes
still flows in her veins.

100
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,720
Over the years,
the Golden Horseshoes

101
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:25,250
have been carried
farther and farther apart.

102
00:04:25,260 --> 00:04:29,020
And because of that,
their magic is weakening.

103
00:04:29,010 --> 00:04:31,840
That's why Mimic
is getting weaker.

104
00:04:31,850 --> 00:04:33,160
Where do we find the Horseshoes?

105
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,600
In the Land of Screera.

106
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:41,600
It's said that the Scree gaze
upon one to see what will be.

107
00:04:41,610 --> 00:04:44,170
Okay, we're going to Screera.

108
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:46,660
Now, while you hunt for
the Horseshoes,

109
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:49,780
Habbit and I will
look after poor Mimic.

110
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:51,610
Won't we Habbit?

111
00:04:51,620 --> 00:04:52,930
Here child.

112
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:56,200
This might prove
of better use to you than me.

113
00:04:58,710 --> 00:05:00,550
Oh now! Dear, dear, dear...
Well, let's see.

114
00:05:00,540 --> 00:05:03,680
I was about to turn
yellow into blue, uh, I think.

115
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:06,550
Oh! Of course, poor Mimic!

116
00:05:06,550 --> 00:05:08,430
Come along, Habbit!

117
