00:06:13,450 --> 00:06:16,000
(North star)
It's over there! That's Screera.

136
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,500
If this is Screera, North Star,

137
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:20,290
where are the Scree?

138
00:06:20,290 --> 00:06:22,000
They're all around us.

139
00:06:22,010 --> 00:06:24,270
(cackles)

140
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:28,010
I'd bet five-to-one
you'd come back, North Star.

141
00:06:28,010 --> 00:06:30,460
I want you all
to meet Fleetfoot,

142
00:06:30,470 --> 00:06:32,360
leader of the Scree.

143
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:35,350
And watcher
of the Crescent of Visions.

144
00:06:35,350 --> 00:06:38,470
That was how I could
predict North Star's return.

145
00:06:38,470 --> 00:06:40,360
Isn't that cheating?

146
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,480
Screes only bet on sure things.

147
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:46,230
But the Crescent of Visions did
not show why you returned.

148
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,380
It's like this...

149
00:06:49,370 --> 00:06:51,870
You see, Mimic,
one of the ponies...

150
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:56,210
The Crescent fell from the sky,
it was a gift to the Scree.

151
00:06:56,210 --> 00:06:58,070
We cannot part with it.

152
00:06:58,080 --> 00:07:01,640
That's the horseshoe,
but what can we do?

153
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:03,460
Shhh...I have an idea.

154
00:07:03,470 --> 00:07:06,090
Fleetfoot, I challenge
you to a race.

155
00:07:06,090 --> 00:07:07,980
The winner gets the Crescent.

156
00:07:07,970 --> 00:07:10,470
On one condition!

157
00:07:10,470 --> 00:07:13,590
If you lose, you become
my servant forever!

158
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:16,090
Done.

159
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:19,860
Oh, poor Wind Whistler,
she looks so embarrassed.

160
00:07:22,850 --> 00:07:25,740
- Come on! Wind Whistler!
- You can do it!

161
00:07:25,740 --> 00:07:27,600
(All cheer)

162
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:33,120
Oh, no!

163
00:07:33,110 --> 00:07:34,410
Oh! Wind Whistler.

164
00:07:39,700 --> 00:07:40,950
(laughs)

165
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:43,000
The Crescent never lies.

166
00:07:43,010 --> 00:07:45,430
It foretold
that Fleetfoot would win.

167
00:07:45,420 --> 00:07:50,460
(cackles)
Of course, we Scree,
only bet on sure things.

168
00:07:50,460 --> 00:07:51,710
Silly ponies!

169
00:07:51,710 --> 00:07:54,850
(both laugh)

170
00:07:54,850 --> 00:07:57,300
So that's what's going on.

171
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:59,550
But they won't get
away with it.

172
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:02,200
<i>(wolves howling)
Wolves scream...</i>

173
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,390
My head's goin' in!

174
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:06,860
<i>(howling continues)</i>

175
00:08:06,860 --> 00:08:09,450
Megan,
what are you doing?

176
00:08:09,450 --> 00:08:10,700
They cheated.

177
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:11,950
They knew Fleetfoot would win.

178
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:13,820
And we need it for Mimic's sake.

179
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:19,080
I say...
These ninnies don't play fair.

180
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,040
It's worth a try.

181
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:25,580
Horseshoe of Visions,
where is the Horseshoe of Light?

182
00:08:26,830 --> 00:08:28,080
That's Blarkland!

183
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:29,970
I've been there.

184
00:08:29,970 --> 00:08:31,800
Great! Show us the way.

185
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:35,590
So you want the Horseshoe
to save your friend, correct?

186
00:08:35,590 --> 00:08:39,180
We Blarks collect, keep,
and trade junk and riddles.

187
00:08:39,180 --> 00:08:40,430
You have no junk.

188
00:08:40,430 --> 00:08:42,930
So, tell me a riddle
I don't know,

189
00:08:42,930 --> 00:08:44,760
and the Horseshoe is yours.

190
00:08:44,770 --> 00:08:46,740
Thank you.
That's very generous.

191
00:08:46,740 --> 00:08:49,910
Uh...why did the boy threw
the alarm clock out the window?

192
00:08:49,910 --> 00:08:52,280
Because he wanted
to see time fly.

193
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:56,040
Tell me one I don't know!

194
00:08:56,030 --> 00:08:57,530
I have a riddle.

195
00:08:57,530 --> 00:08:59,410
What walks on four legs
in the morning,

196
00:08:59,420 --> 00:09:02,540
two at mid day,
and three at sunset?

197
00:09:02,540 --> 00:09:05,340
Uh...a three-toed bullfrog?

198
00:09:05,340 --> 00:09:08,430
No...uh,
a dragon with gooseflesh?

199
00:09:08,420 --> 00:09:11,510
Um-uh, a gyrating galumpadillo?

200
00:09:11,510 --> 00:09:12,840
I guess not...

201
00:09:12,850 --> 00:09:14,100
I give up!

202
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,350
What?!

203
00:09:15,350 --> 00:09:17,060
Humans, like Megan.

204
00:09:17,050 --> 00:09:18,930
They crawl as babies,

205
00:09:18,940 --> 00:09:20,190
they walk as adults,

206
00:09:20,190 --> 00:09:22,610
and they use a cane
for a third foot

207
00:09:22,610 --> 00:09:24,560
when they grow very old.

208
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:27,900
(laughs)
Very good!

209
00:09:27,890 --> 00:09:30,390
Cracker, take them
to the Horseshoe.

210
00:09:31,650 --> 00:09:34,160
It's here, umm...
somewhere.

211
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:36,650
We'll never find it in all this.

212
00:09:36,650 --> 00:09:37,530
Everyone listen!

213
00:09:37,540 --> 00:09:40,130
This horseshoe
has the power of light,

214
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,370
so that's what we look for.

215
00:09:41,370 --> 00:09:44,490
You mean like
the one by Cracker's foot?

216
00:09:44,490 --> 00:09:45,620
I'll get it out!

217
00:09:46,330 --> 00:09:47,540
Uh-oh!

218
00:09:47,550 --> 00:09:48,840
Look out!

219
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:53,470
You saved Cracker.

220
00:09:53,470 --> 00:09:57,250
So I order a hole to be dug
to the Goblin tunnels.

221
00:09:57,260 --> 00:09:59,770
There you will find
another Horseshoe,

222
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:02,890
stolen a long time ago
from the Blarks.

223
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:03,900
Thank you for your help.

224
00:10:03,900 --> 00:10:05,240
No problem.

225
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:08,350
You are all the Blarks' friends.

226
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,850
Megan, look!

227
00:10:10,850 --> 00:10:12,740
The Horseshoe is growing
brighter.

228
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:14,600
We must be nearing
the third one.

229
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:17,990
Now, what have we here?

230
00:10:17,990 --> 00:10:21,110
Won't Ma be surprised?

231
00:10:21,110 --> 00:10:22,500
(murmuring)

